dex.html, styles.css) and backend (server.py, api/) components, along with data files (data.json, us_market.json, chat_history.json).","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Listing of project root directory structure","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:47:17.110Z","title":"Directory listing for stock-dashboard project","type":"file_read"},"obs_mr9t8kck_ad5fa2caef8a":{"concepts":["patch application","system hooks","state change notification"],"confidence":0.9,"facts":["Hook type: patch_applied","Timestamp: 2026-07-06T22:47:17.209Z"],"files":[],"id":"obs_mr9t8kck_ad5fa2caef8a","importance":5,"narrative":"A patch_applied hook was triggered at the specified timestamp, indicating that a code or configuration patch has been successfully applied to the system. This notification serves as a state change event that may impact subsequent operations or require validation of the applied changes.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"System notification indicating a patch was successfully applied","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:47:17.209Z","title":"Patch applied via hook","type":"notification"},"obs_mr9t8kck_aa421e9322ad":{"concepts":["hook event","workflow step"],"confidence":0.9,"facts":["Hook type: step_finish","Timestamp: 2026-07-06T22:47:17.191Z"],"files":[],"id":"obs_mr9t8kck_aa421e9322ad","importance":1,"narrative":"A step_finish hook was triggered, indicating completion of a workflow step. No additional tool usage or context was provided in the observation.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"step_finish hook triggered at 2026-07-06T22:47:17.191Z","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:47:17.191Z","title":"Step completion hook received","type":"notification"},"obs_mr9t8n5q_b2f6d99a1d1d":{"concepts":["Python HTTP server","stock data API integration","AI provider routing","technical indicator caching","realtime volatility detection","environment-based API keys"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Uses Python http.server with SimpleHTTPRequestHandler and ThreadingHTTPServer","Integrates Naver Finance realtime API (NAVER_REALTIME_URL) and KRX API","Supports four AI providers: ZAI, NOUS, OpenRouter, OpenCode with environment-based keys","Implements caching: technical indicators (5min TTL, max 60) and AI responses (5min TTL)","Tracks price history for real-time volatility detection (60 data points, ~10 minutes)","Configuration loaded from data.json; chat history persisted to chat_history.json","Default KRX API key present in code; NOUS_KEY shows [REDACTED_SECRET] placeholder"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/server.py"],"id":"obs_mr9t8n5q_b2f6d99a1d1d","importance":7,"narrative":"The file contains the main backend server for a Korean stock dashboard application. It provides HTTP endpoints to serve the frontend and proxy requests to Naver Finance for realtime stock quotes and the KRX API for market data. The server also acts as an AI chat backend, routing requests to multiple LLM providers with response caching and technical indicator calculations based on price history.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"HTTP server with Naver Finance, KRX API, and multiple AI provider integrations","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:47:20.892Z","title":"Stock dashboard Python server implementation","type":"file_read"},"obs_mr9t8n86_c730f98c5b90":{"concepts":["localStorage persistence","Intl.NumberFormat locale formatting","vanilla JavaScript DOM manipulation","modal management pattern","client-side state management","sidebar resize UX pattern"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Uses Intl.NumberFormat with 'ko-KR' locale for currency and percentage formatting","Manages 19 DOM element references including modals, tables, and buttons","Persists ordering via localStorage keys: stock_holdings_order_v2, stock_watchlist_order_v2, sidebarWidth","Implements sortBySavedOrder function using Map and localStorage for stable ordering","Contains sidebar resize/toggle logic with overlay and body overflow control","State includes autoTimer, newsTimer, aiResults Map, profitHistory array","Defines SIDEBAR_REFRESH_INTERVAL constant at 300000ms (5 minutes)"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/app.js"],"id":"obs_mr9t8n86_c730f98c5b90","importance":4,"narrative":"The main application file for a Korean stock dashboard implements client-side UI state management using vanilla JavaScript. It provides persistent ordering for holdings and watchlist through localStorage, sidebar resizing with saved width preferences, and Korean locale number formatting. The file also manages modal components and auto-refresh timers for data updates.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Vanilla JS stock dashboard with Korean locale formatting and localStorage persistence","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:47:20.980Z","title":"Main stock dashboard app.js structure","type":"file_read"},"obs_mr9t8nc6_57a46f9e6a1d":{"concepts":["Python project structure","API backend scaffolding","stock dashboard backend"],"confidence":0.9,"facts":["Target directory path: /home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api","Directory contains 2 entries: __pycache__/ subdirectory and index.py file"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api"],"id":"obs_mr9t8nc6_57a46f9e6a1d","importance":2,"narrative":"We read the contents of the stock-dashboard project's api directory to evaluate its existing structure, finding only a compiled Python cache directory and a single index.py entry point file, indicating a minimal initial API setup with no additional backend modules present.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Initial scan of project backend API directory structure","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:47:21.124Z","title":"List stock-dashboard API directory contents","type":"file_read"},"obs_mr9t8rz2_b5ebb7a14ffe":{"concepts":["LLM prompt engineering","caching strategies","technical analysis scoring","fallback mechanisms","stock market data aggregation"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Technical signal scoring uses threshold of 15 points to override AI \"hold\" signals","US market analysis function calls LLM with index data and news to generate Korean summary and highlights","Analysis results cached in _us_analysis_cache with date key, highlights limited to 3 items","Fallback functions _fallback_highlights and _fallback_summary used when LLM fails","US indices tracked: Dow Jones (DJI@DJI), S&P 500 (SPI@SPX), Nasdaq (NAS@IXIC), Philadelphia Semiconductor (SOX@SOX)","Chat history limit set to 20 messages (CHAT_MSG_LIMIT)","Technical signals limited to top 3 added to result reasons"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/server.py"],"id":"obs_mr9t8rz2_b5ebb7a14ffe","importance":6,"narrative":"Read a section of the stock dashboard server showing the AI-powered US market analysis feature. The code generates daily market summaries by combining index data and news into an LLM prompt, with Korean language output and robust caching. Technical stock signals use a scoring system where scores >=15 can override AI \"hold\" recommendations.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Reading offset 1304 of server.py showing LLM-based US market analysis and technical signal scoring","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:47:27.132Z","title":"Stock dashboard server - US market analysis code","type":"file_read"},"obs_mr9t8s36_0f6e1ca3b297":{"concepts":["Flask API","Upstash Redis REST client","AI provider routing","API key hardcoding","In-memory caching TTL","Stock dashboard backend"],"confidence":1,"facts":["File path: /home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api/index.py","Flask app initialized with static_folder=None","Uses Upstash Redis REST API via urllib for key-value operations (kv_get, kv_set)","Data files: data.json, chat_history.json, us_market.json","Four AI providers configured: ZAI (Zhipu), NOUS Research, OpenRouter, OpenCode","AI cache dictionary with TTL=300 seconds","KRX API key has hardcoded default value","ZAI_KEY contains visible hardcoded bearer token","File content truncated at line 102 inside load_config() function"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api/index.py"],"id":"obs_mr9t8s36_0f6e1ca3b297","importance":8,"narrative":"This is the main API entry point for a stock dashboard application. It implements a Flask backend with Upstash Redis for persistent storage and supports multiple AI inference providers (ZAI, NOUS, OpenRouter, OpenCode) with a cache layer. The code shows a multi-provider strategy with model lists for free-tier endpoints, though it contains hardcoded API keys which is a security concern. The file is truncated so the load_config logic and route handlers are not fully visible.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Partial view of index.py showing Redis, AI model routing, and API key management","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:47:27.278Z","title":"Flask stock dashboard API with multi-provider AI integration","type":"file_read"},"obs_mr9t9071_a10e30132765":{"concepts":["session management","Redis persistence","data migration","serverless architecture","chat history"],"confidence":1,"facts":["SESSION_TIMEOUT_MS = 3600000 (60 minutes)","Uses Upstash Redis as primary storage with filesystem fallback","Normalizes legacy data formats (raw list â {sessions, current} envelope)","KST timezone used for session date/time generation","Serverless-safe: no in-memory cache, always reads fresh from Redis"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api/index.py"],"id":"obs_mr9t9071_a10e30132765","importance":3,"narrative":"Read the session persistence layer showing how chat sessions are loaded, saved, and auto-expired after 60 minutes of inactivity. The code handles migration from older data formats and supports both Redis and local filesystem storage.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Lines 1291-1378 of chat session handling logic","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:47:37.784Z","title":"Read session management code in api/index.py","type":"file_read"},"obs_mr9t96hf_0d24f197b26b":{"concepts":["DuckDuckGo search API","Brave Search API","stock news filtering","Korean web search","result deduplication","financial NLP","web scraping"],"confidence":1,"facts":["File path: /home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api/index.py","Read offset: 2518 (continuation of file)","Contains is_irrelevant_result() function for filtering non-stock content","Wikipedia URLs filtered unless they contain stock keywords (stock, ėĢžė, kospi, kosdaq, vi, volatility, finance, market, invest, trading, ë°°ëđ, ėėĨ, ęģĩë§Īë, ėĄëĐī, ëģë, íļėŽ, ėėŽ)","Results with text &lt; 20 characters are skipped","search_web_ddg() uses duckduckgo_search.DDGS with 3 Korean query variations","Queries include: \"{query} íęĩ­ ėĢžė 2026\", \"{query} ėĶė ė ë§\", \"ėĢžė {query[:150]}\"","DDG results limited to max 8 items, deduplicated via seen_urls set","search_web_brave() calls Brave Search API for news (freshness=pw, count=5) and web search","Brave API authenticated via X-Subscription-Token header using BRAVE_API_KEY","Both search functions truncate result text to 2000 characters"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api/index.py"],"id":"obs_mr9t96hf_0d24f197b26b","importance":6,"narrative":"This read reveals the web search component of a stock dashboard API located in api/index.py. The implementation provides dual-source web search capabilities using DuckDuckGo and Brave Search APIs, specifically tailored for Korean stock market news and information. A relevance filtering system ensures only stock-related content is returned by excluding Wikipedia pages without financial keywords and short text entries.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"DuckDuckGo and Brave Search API integration with relevance filtering","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:47:45.936Z","title":"Web search implementation for Korean stock news","type":"file_read"},"obs_mr9t96mm_b3e3a18835e3":{"concepts":["Vercel deployment configuration","serverless Python backend","static asset serving","API route proxying"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Build entry for api/index.py using @vercel/python builder","Static file handling for .html, .js, .css, and .json files using @vercel/static","Route /api/(.*) mapped to /api/index.py","Route / mapped to /index.html","Catch-all route /(.*) mapped to /$1 for static serving"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/vercel.json"],"id":"obs_mr9t96mm_b3e3a18835e3","importance":6,"narrative":"Read the Vercel configuration file which defines the deployment strategy for this stock dashboard project. The setup uses a Python backend API alongside static file serving for frontend assets. Any requests to /api/* are routed to the Python handler in api/index.py, while all other paths serve static files from the project root.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Python backend with static asset serving setup","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:47:46.124Z","title":"Vercel deployment configuration","type":"file_read"},"obs_mr9t9l0s_9f92292d78fd":{"concepts":["ZAI API","rate limiting","API quota exhaustion","glm-5 model"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Error code: 1310","Error message: Weekly/Monthly Limit Exhausted","Limit resets at: 2026-07-08 08:29:53","Model tested: glm-5","Endpoint: https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4/chat/completions"],"files":[],"id":"obs_mr9t9l0s_9f92292d78fd","importance":5,"narrative":"A direct curl test of the ZAI API was attempted to validate API connectivity. The request returned error code 1310 indicating that the weekly/monthly usage quota has been fully consumed. The service will remain unavailable until the quota resets on 2026-07-08 at 08:29:53.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"API quota exceeded for glm-5 model","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:48:04.778Z","title":"ZAI API rate limit exhausted","type":"error"},"obs_mr9t9ljg_def9db31dd39":{"concepts":["API authentication","curl testing","REST API"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Request sent to https://opencode.ai/zen/go/v1/chat/completions","Model specified: glm-5.2","Response: {\"type\":\"error\",\"error\":{\"type\":\"AuthError\",\"message\":\"Missing API key.\"}}","Timeout configured: 10s connect, 30s max"],"files":[],"id":"obs_mr9t9ljg_def9db31dd39","importance":4,"narrative":"Attempted to test OpenCode API connectivity by sending a curl request to the chat completions endpoint without providing an API key. The request failed with an authentication error, confirming the API requires valid credentials. This validates that the endpoint is reachable but not publicly accessible.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Curl request to OpenCode AI chat completions endpoint","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:48:05.449Z","title":"Test OpenCode API without authentication","type":"command_run"},"obs_mr9t9sa2_5a063d02e968":{"concepts":["REST API authentication","HTTP 401 errors","OpenRouter API","curl testing"],"confidence":1,"facts":["HTTP 401 error returned from https://openrouter.ai/api/v1/chat/completions","Error message: \"No cookie auth credentials found\"","Model attempted: nex-agi/nex-n2-pro:free","No API key was included in the request headers"],"files":[],"id":"obs_mr9t9sa2_5a063d02e968","importance":2,"narrative":"A curl POST request was made to the OpenRouter API without authentication credentials. The server responded with a 401 status code indicating that cookie authentication credentials were not found. This confirms that OpenRouter requires valid authentication for API access.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Test request to OpenRouter chat completions endpoint without API key failed","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:48:14.185Z","title":"OpenRouter API returns 401 - No auth credentials","type":"error"},"obs_mr9t9yjb_a59f94dacbe4":{"concepts":["REST API testing","reasoning tokens","Nous Research inference API","Chat Completions API","BYOK authentication"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Endpoint: https://inference-api.nousresearch.com/v1/chat/completions","Model: stepfun/step-3.7-flash:free (provider: StepFun)","Request sent \"Say hello\" with max_tokens=50","finish_reason: length (max tokens reached)","Prompt tokens: 14, completion tokens: 50, total: 64","Response cost: $0.00005 (upstream: $0.0000603)","Reasoning content exposed in message.content: null with reasoning text present","Service tier: null, system_fingerprint: null","is_byok: true (BYOK enabled)"],"files":[],"id":"obs_mr9t9yjb_a59f94dacbe4","importance":5,"narrative":"A curl command successfully tested the Nous Research API using the free StepFun step-3.7-flash model. The response revealed that reasoning tokens are counted and exposed in the API response structure, with content: null but reasoning_text populated. The request hit the max_tokens limit (50) causing finish_reason: length, truncating the reasoning output.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"POST request to Nous inference API with free StepFun model","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:48:22.293Z","title":"Test Nous Research Chat Completions API","type":"command_run"},"obs_mr9ta4v5_6a3a11ac30b9":{"concepts":["LLM inference API","NousResearch","OpenRouter catalog","model availability checking","404 error handling"],"confidence":1,"facts":["POST request sent to https://inference-api.nousresearch.com/v1/chat/completions","Model requested: \"openai/gpt-oss-120b:free\"","HTTP 404 response received","Error: \"Model not found in our configuration or OpenRouter catalog\""],"files":[],"id":"obs_mr9ta4v5_6a3a11ac30b9","importance":3,"narrative":"Attempted to test NousResearch's inference API endpoint with the openai/gpt-oss-120b:free model. The API returned a 404 status indicating the model does not exist in either NousResearch's configuration or the OpenRouter catalog. This model is currently unavailable for testing through this endpoint.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Attempted to query openai/gpt-oss-120b:free via NousResearch inference API","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:48:30.495Z","title":"NousResearch API model test returns 404","type":"command_run"},"obs_mr9ta5m9_4df146fd8b46":{"concepts":["Nous Research API","model availability","OpenRouter catalog","HTTP 404 error"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Endpoint: https://inference-api.nousresearch.com/v1/chat/completions","Model tested: nex-agi/nex-n2-pro:free","Error: 404 - Model not found","Error indicates model doesn't exist in configuration or OpenRouter catalog","Request timeout: 30 seconds, connect timeout: 10 seconds"],"files":[],"id":"obs_mr9ta5m9_4df146fd8b46","importance":4,"narrative":"A curl command tested the Nous Research inference API with the model \"nex-agi/nex-n2-pro:free\" and received a 404 response. The API returned that the requested model does not exist in their configuration or the OpenRouter catalog, suggesting the model name may be incorrect or not available through this endpoint.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"curl POST to Nous inference API with nex-2-n-pro model","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:48:31.470Z","title":"Nous API model test returns 404","type":"command_run"},"obs_mr9tajxq_1d034de8a849":{"concepts":["API client resilience","response parsing","fallback handling","LLM integration"],"confidence":1,"facts":["File: /home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api/index.py","Function modified: chat_from_nous","max_tokens increased from 1500 to 2500","Added fallback: content = msg.get(\"reasoning\") or \"\" when content is empty"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api/index.py"],"id":"obs_mr9tajxq_1d034de8a849","importance":4,"narrative":"The chat_from_nous function was updated to handle cases where the Nous API returns an empty content field by falling back to the \"reasoning\" field. Additionally, the max_tokens parameter was increased from 1500 to 2500 to allow longer responses.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Update chat_from_nous to handle empty content with reasoning fallback","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:48:50.025Z","title":"Improve Nous API response parsing resilience","type":"file_edit"},"obs_mr9tarin_74002a7aff69":{"concepts":["LLM fallback chain","multi-provider AI","error handling","urllib HTTP requests"],"confidence":1,"facts":["File: /home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api/index.py","Function call_llm implements multi-provider LLM fallback chain","Provider order: OpenCode GLM-5.2 â zai glm-5 â OpenCode GLM-5.1 â nous models â openrouter models","Each provider failure is logged to stderr with [call_llm] prefix","Final fallback returns Korean error message when all providers exhausted"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api/index.py"],"id":"obs_mr9tarin_74002a7aff69","importance":7,"narrative":"The edit modifies the core call_llm function which manages fallback logic across multiple LLM providers. This function is critical infrastructure for the stock dashboard's AI features. The change alters the provider chain logic, though the full new implementation details are truncated in the observation.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Modifying call_llm function in stock dashboard API","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:48:59.850Z","title":"Multi-provider LLM fallback chain modification","type":"file_edit"},"obs_mr9taxug_71eb6b448d25":{"concepts":["API response parsing","LLM provider integration","fallback handling"],"confidence":1,"facts":["File: /home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/server.py","Function: chat_from_nous(messages, model=None)","Added fallback: msg.get(\"reasoning\") or \"\" when content is empty/None","Uses _strip_thinking_artifacts() to clean response text"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/server.py"],"id":"obs_mr9taxug_71eb6b448d25","importance":5,"narrative":"Edited the Nous API integration to handle cases where the model returns a \"reasoning\" field instead of \"content\". The function now gracefully falls back to the reasoning field before returning an error, improving compatibility with different Nous model response formats.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Added fallback to check \"reasoning\" field when \"content\" is empty in Nous API responses","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:49:08.052Z","title":"Nous API response fallback for reasoning field","type":"file_edit"},"obs_mr9tb5ie_242657d5acff":{"concepts":["LLM fallback chain","no-op edit detection","server-side LLM routing"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Tool: edit","File: /home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/server.py","Error: oldString and newString are identical","Function modified: call_llm(messages) with 4-provider fallback chain"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/server.py"],"id":"obs_mr9tb5ie_242657d5acff","importance":2,"narrative":"The edit tool failed because the proposed change contained identical oldString and newString values, resulting in a no-op. The target function call_llm implements a cascading fallback strategy across OpenCode GLM-5.2, ZAI GLM-5, Nous models, and OpenRouter models.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"No-op edit attempted on call_llm function","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:49:17.985Z","title":"Failed edit: identical old and new strings","type":"error"},"obs_mr9tbmmp_1a2715185854":{"concepts":["reasoning field fallback","Nous Research API","reasoning models","DeepSeek R1 style reasoning","Korean stock market analysis"],"confidence":1,"facts":["API endpoint: https://inference-api.nousresearch.com/v1/chat/completions","Model: stepfun/step-3.7-flash:free","Response content field: None","Response reasoning field: Contains Korean reasoning text about stock market analysis","Reasoning discusses: US rate cut expectations, semiconductor industry, geopolitical risks, Q2 earnings season","Request was in Korean asking for domestic stock market outlook"],"files":["N/A (bash command execution)"],"id":"obs_mr9tbmmp_1a2715185854","importance":8,"narrative":"The test sent a Korean request to Nous Research's inference API using the stepfun/step-3.7-flash:free model. The response returned None in the content field but populated the reasoning field with the model's thought process about analyzing Korean stock market factors (US rates, semiconductors, geopolitical tensions, earnings season).","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Testing if Nous API returns reasoning field when content is None","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:49:40.173Z","title":"Test Nous Reasoning Fallback Response","type":"command_run"},"obs_mr9tbrti_cb7fdf54ca4c":{"concepts":["fallback pattern","cascading providers","character encoding fallback","AI chat routing","Korean i18n","citation formatting"],"confidence":1,"facts":["16 matches found in /home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api/index.py","Redis persistence with filesystem fallback at line 1333","Naver API UTF-8/EUC-KR/CP949 fallback decoding at line 128","AI provider fallback chain: primary â zai glm-5 â nous â error message at lines 2379-2421","Fallback highlights/summary functions defined at lines 1492, 1502","chat_with_ai function defined at line 2637 with citation handling (ėķėē) at lines 2725, 2729","System prompt requires citations with sources at line 2707"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api/index.py"],"id":"obs_mr9tbrti_cb7fdf54ca4c","importance":6,"narrative":"The grep search revealed multiple fallback mechanisms throughout the API: data persistence falls back from Redis to filesystem, AI providers cascade through zai glm-5 and nous before showing an error, and Naver API responses handle multiple encodings. The chat_with_ai module also implements Korean citation (ėķėē) stripping and formatting logic.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Grep for chat_with_ai|ėķėē|fallback in api/index.py","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:49:46.894Z","title":"Search results for fallback and AI chat patterns","type":"search"},"obs_mr9tclgh_6fd5031ecda3":{"concepts":["reasoning models","chain-of-thought","Nous Research API","max_tokens limits","API response structure"],"confidence":1,"facts":["API endpoint: https://inference-api.nousresearch.com/v1/chat/completions","Model: stepfun/step-3.7-flash:free","Response content length: 0 characters","Response reasoning length: 3675 characters","Finish reason: length (max_tokens reached)","Model returned reasoning field but empty content field","Working directory: /home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard"],"id":"obs_mr9tclgh_6fd5031ecda3","importance":7,"narrative":"A test call to the Nous Research inference API using the stepfun/step-3.7-flash:free model was made with a Korean stock market query. The model returned its chain-of-thought reasoning (3675 chars) in a separate 'reasoning' field but produced zero characters in the 'content' field because it hit the max_tokens limit. This reveals the model is a reasoning-style model that exposes internal monologue separately from final output, requiring careful token budget management.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Testing Nous Research API with Korean stock market query","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:50:25.308Z","title":"Nous API test reveals reasoning model behavior","type":"command_run"},"obs_mr9td7fm_b40f28f290d6":{"concepts":["LLM API integration","API response validation","Chat completions"],"confidence":1,"facts":["Model: stepfun/step-3.7-flash:free","Endpoint: https://inference-api.nousresearch.com/v1/chat/completions","max_tokens: 8000","Response content length: 501 characters","Response reasoning length: 1601 characters","finish_reason: stop","Response language: Korean"],"files":[],"id":"obs_mr9td7fm_b40f28f290d6","importance":5,"narrative":"Executed a Python script to test the Nous Research API with the stepfun/step-3.7-flash:free model, requesting 8000 max_tokens. The API successfully returned a Korean-language response containing both content and reasoning fields, with finish_reason=\"stop\". The content provided a Korean stock market outlook.","sessionId":"ses_0