xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Security improvement in stock dashboard API","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:56:31.778Z","title":"Replace hardcoded ZAI_KEY with env var lookup","type":"file_edit"},"obs_mr9tkk3y_aa950de663b8":{"concepts":["environment variables","API key management","secret configuration"],"confidence":1,"facts":["ZAI_KEY uses env var with empty default","KRX_API_KEY uses env var with hardcoded default: D3ABD30920534A2C9616A984AB6078D1C722F0BA","NOUS_KEY uses env var with placeholder default","OPENROUTER_KEY, OPENCODE_KEY, BRAVE_API_KEY use env vars with empty defaults","All assignments use os.environ.get() pattern"],"files":["api/index.py"],"id":"obs_mr9tkk3y_aa950de663b8","importance":6,"narrative":"Verified that the codebase uses environment variables for API key storage. Most keys properly require environment variables (empty string defaults), but KRX_API_KEY has a hardcoded fallback value, which is a potential security concern.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Security audit of key storage patterns","timestamp":"2026-07-06T22:56:36.810Z","title":"API key assignments using environment variables","type":"search"},"obs_mr9tkpj0_9881b08fc9f7":{"concepts":["LLM model configuration","OpenRouter API aliases","Model fallback strategy"],"confidence":1,"facts":["File modified: /home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api/index.py","NOUS_MODELS changed from 3 entries to 1 entry","Remaining model: stepfun/step-3.7-flash:free","Removed models: nex-agi/nex-n2-pro:free, openai/gpt-oss-120b:free"],"files":["/home/rg3270/blog/stock-dashboard/api/index.py"],"id":"obs_mr9tkpj0_9881b08fc9f7","importance":4,"narrative":"The AI model configuration was simplified by removing two additional model options, leaving only 'stepfun/step-3.7-flash:free' in the NOUS_MODELS list. This potentially restricts API requests to a single model path rather than allowing fallback or selection from multiple models.","sessionId":"ses_0c662c7c3ffe67rW13w0xXA3Xf","subtitle":"Restrict AI m